<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07858</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT TO PROVIDE YOUTH SUICIDE INTERVENTION AND PREVENTION</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Mandates the Department of Education (DepEd), in coordination with the Department of Health (DOH), to formulate and include a course of Life Planning in the elementary and secondary education curriculum which shall require lectures and discussion on self and identity; personal, family, community values; communication and interrelationship with others; sexuality and gender roles; community participation; health; psychological thinking and employment, among others.  It requires all schools to implement a Peer Counselling Program that includes the Peer Counselling Training Course and the Mentor-Mentee Program. This bill also mandates DOH to employ at least one (1) psychologist in every school that shall be required to visit the school at least once (1) a month to hold School Counselling Alignment Sessions.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VILLAFUERTE, LUIS RAYMUND JR. F.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-06-07</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (000 2018-08-15)</td><td>2. Del Mar (000 2018-08-15)</td><tr><td>3. Lopez (M.L.) (000 2018-08-15)</td><td>4. Vergara (000 2018-08-15)</td><tr><td>5. Sy-Alvarado (000 2018-09-10)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>